/span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> requirements.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50.33pt; padding-left:3.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Public awareness needs to be raised and this is best done by the maintenance of a single register of all Competent Persons Scheme m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">embers.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> If an accreditation body refuses to accept this, they should be removed from the scheme.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 51.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Legislation is useless without enforcement. LABC’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s should be directed by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the DCLG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to take ownership of compliance in existing dwellings.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> This is where the maj</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ori</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ty of work covered by Part P of the Building Regulations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> bei